Below is the change Apache MyFaces Core 1.2.9 made to fix CVE-2010-2057. StateUtils now adds a Message Authentication Code (HmacSHA1 by default) to the encrypted ViewState using an encrypt-then-MAC composition, and verifies the MAC BEFORE decrypting:

**File: StateUtils.java (Apache MyFaces shared-impl 3.0.8, shipped in Core 1.2.9 -- the fix relative to 3.0.7)**
