OWASP ESAPI is a security *library*. The code below is the change OWASP ESAPI 2.0 made to fix CVE-2010-3300. ESAPI 2.0 switched to authenticated encryption: JavaEncryptor.decrypt() validates a Message Authentication Code (HmacSHA1 over IV || ciphertext, under a separate derived authentication key) BEFORE decrypting:

**File: JavaEncryptor.java + CryptoHelper.java (OWASP ESAPI 2.0GA)**
```java
public PlainText decrypt(SecretKey key, CipherText ciphertext)
    throws EncryptionException, IllegalArgumentException
{
    // ... argument and cipher-mode checks ...
    PlainText plaintext = null;
    boolean caughtException = false;
    int progressMark = 0;
    try {
        // First we validate the MAC.
        boolean valid = CryptoHelper.isCipherTextMACvalid(key, ciphertext);
        if ( !valid ) {
            try {
                // This is going to fail, but we want the same processing
                // to occur as much as possible so as to prevent timing attacks.
                handleDecryption(key, ciphertext); // Ignore return (should fail).
            } catch(Exception ex) {
                ;   // Ignore
            }
            throw new EncryptionException(DECRYPTION_FAILED,
                    "Decryption failed because MAC invalid for " + ciphertext);
        }
        progressMark++;
        // The decryption only counts if the MAC was valid.
        plaintext = handleDecryption(key, ciphertext);
        progressMark++;
    } catch(EncryptionException ex) {
        // ... timing-equalised error handling ...
        throw ex;
    }
    // ... finally: sleep to equalise timing ...
    return plaintext;
}

public static boolean isCipherTextMACvalid(SecretKey sk, CipherText ct)
{
    if ( CryptoHelper.isMACRequired( ct ) ) {
        try {
            SecretKey authKey = CryptoHelper.computeDerivedKey( sk, ct.getKeySize(), "authenticity");
            boolean validMAC = ct.validateMAC( authKey );
            return validMAC;
        } catch (Exception ex) {
            // Error on side of security. If this fails and can't verify MAC assume it is invalid.
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}
```
