AES-GCM is an authenticated encryption mode: encryption computes a 128-bit authentication tag over the ciphertext and appends it, and decryption recomputes and checks that tag before returning any bytes. If a single bit of the cookie is altered, the check fails and the JCE raises AEADBadTagException, which CookieRememberMeManager surfaces as a rejected cookie -- no plaintext, and no partial result, is ever produced.

